anagement, referring to investor demand for buyout debt. =E2=80=9CGiven the=
 incremental company specific news flow since the deal was agreed to -- com=
bined with the meaningful deterioration in the economy -- lenders will be v=
ery hesitant to provide financing.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For comparison, the private equity buyout of C=
itrix Systems Inc. was signed in January, and last month banks sold most of=
 the $15 billion of debt for the deal at prices of <a href=3D"https://link.=
mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29273685.287528/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZX=
JnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDktMjAvY2l0cml4LW9mZmVycy1zdGVlcGVyLWRpc=
2NvdW50cy1vbi1idXlvdXQtZGVidC10by1sdXJlLWludmVzdG9ycz9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMDA1MjJf=
TU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGV=
ybT0yMjEwMDUmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB86395=
a99" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">  83.5 to 91 cents</a> on the dollar. Similar levels here woul=
d leave Musk=E2=80=99s banks with more than a billion dollars of losses.</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Ordinarily when banks provide debt financing f=
or a leveraged buyout, there is an orderly process for marketing the debt. =
Between signing and closing of the deal everyone =E2=80=94=C2=A0the banks, =
the target, the buyer =E2=80=94=C2=A0gets together and writes disclosure an=
d marketing documents for the debt. The buyer and the target have a busines=
s plan and financial projections that they can pitch to potential investors=
, and they have meetings with those investors to drum up enthusiasm. And th=
en the debt is sold=C2=A0<em>before=C2=A0</em>the deal closes, so that the =
banks have the money (from selling the debt) to give to the buyer to pay th=
e purchase price at closing.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You can read Musk=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https:/=
/link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29273685.287528/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2Vj=
Lmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTEwNDY1OTIyMDQ5ODQ0L3RtMjI=
xMzE4OWQ4X2V4OTktaC5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd6505a5c" itemprop=3D"Sto=
ryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; =
text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-c=
olor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> debt c=
ommitment letter</a> for the deal here. On pages 3 and 4 there is a section=
 titled =E2=80=9CSyndication=E2=80=9D that says that the banks =E2=80=9Cint=
end to commence syndication efforts promptly=E2=80=9D and sell the debt =E2=
=80=9Cprior to the Closing Date,=E2=80=9D and that requires Musk to do thin=
gs like =E2=80=9Censure that any syndication efforts benefit materially fro=
m your existing lending and investment banking relationships,=E2=80=9D =E2=
=80=9Ccause the Company to assist in the preparation of customary confident=
ial information memoranda=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Cother marketing materials,=
=E2=80=9D try to get the debt rated by ratings agencies,=C2=A0and attend at=
 least one meeting for prospective investors, =E2=80=9Cwhich meeting shall =
not exceed two (2) hours in duration and may be virtual.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But the letter also says that =E2=80=9Cthe Ini=
tial Lenders=E2=80=99 commitments hereunder are not conditioned upon the sy=
ndication,=E2=80=9D and it goes on:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Notwithstanding anything to the co=
ntrary contained in this Commitment Letter or the Fee Letter or any other l=
etter agreement or undertaking concerning the financing of the Transactions=
 to the contrary, neither the obtaining of the ratings referenced above nor=
 the compliance with any of the other provisions set forth in clauses (a)=
=C2=A0through (f)=C2=A0above or any other provision of this paragraph shall=
 constitute a condition to the commitments hereunder or the funding of the =
Facilities on the Closing Date or at any time thereafter.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Musk agreed to help the banks sell this debt, =
but=C2=A0<em>even if he doesn=E2=80=99t help=C2=A0</em>they still have to p=
ut up the $13 billion themselves. He didn=E2=80=99t help =E2=80=94=C2=A0he =
hindered! =E2=80=94=C2=A0and here they are. If Musk and Twitter really are =
trying to close this deal within a few days, then the banks will have to pr=
ovide bridge financing: They=E2=80=99ll just lend Twitter the $13 billion o=
f their own money, and =E2=80=9Ctake out=E2=80=9D the bridge financing late=
r by doing a bond offering to investors. Hopefully with some investor meeti=
ngs and marketing materials =E2=80=94 hopefully with Musk at least saying n=
ice things about Twitter again =E2=80=94=C2=A0but who knows.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also, what about the=C2=A0<em>equity=C2=A0</em=
>financing? Right now Musk=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/29273685.287528/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGlu=
aW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDUtMjYvZWxvbi1jYWxsZWQtb2ZmLWhpcy1tYXJnaW4tbG9hbj9=
